HIT ME UP.Definition: contact me, send a message or give a call

PASSIONS.Definition: an extreme interest in or wish for doing something, such as a hobby, activity, etc.

INVEST.Definition: to put money, effort, time, etc.

AUTOMATING.Definition: to make something operate automatically by using machines or computers

AUTOPILOT.Definition: state or condition in which activity or behavior is regulated automatically in a predetermined or instinctive manner

CHARGE.Definition: to ask an amount of money for something, especially a service or activity

DILIGENCE.Definition: working carefully and with a lot of effort

WALKING THE ROAD LESS TRAVELED.Definition: a choice made in one's life that is unconventional, a choice that leads one in a different direction than most people

CREATIVES.Definition: a person whose job involves producing original ideas or doing artistic work

GO AGAINST THE GRAIN.Definition: to do something that is different from what is normal or usual

INEVITABLY.Definition: in a way that cannot be avoided

HIT A WALL.Definition: to reach a point where you feel unable to continue doing something because it is very difficult

NAIVELY.Definition: too willing to believe that someone is telling the truth, that people's intentions in general are good, or that life is simple and fair

INFLUENCERS.Definition: a person with the ability to influence potential buyers of a product or service by promoting or recommending the items on social media

PERSEVERANCE.Definition: continued effort to do or achieve something, even when this is difficult or takes a long time

FREESTYLING.Definition: to talk without having planned what you are going to say

MENTALITY.Definition: a person's particular way of thinking about things

DELUSIONAL.Definition: believing things that are not true
